  "page": null,
  "source": "[\\set.theoretic.range{R}]\nDefines: N is \\set\nwhen: R is \\set\nexpresses:\n. forAll: b is \\set\n  then:\n  . have: b \"in\" N\n    iff:\n    . exists: a is \\set\n      suchThat: \\set.theoretic.ordered.pair:of{a}:and{b} \"in\" R\nDocumented:\n. called: \"range of $R?$\"\n. written: \"\\operatorname{ran}(R?)\"\n. description: \"The range of a relation $R$, the set $\\{b \\mid \\exists a \\text{ such that } a \\mathbin{R} b\\}$ of second coordinates of the pairs in $R$.\"\nId: \"1e82710d-02f0-411a-889b-45bb0f9258ef\"",
